public interface SearchTree<E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>>
Interface to define a search tree

  • Method Details

    • add

      boolean add​(E item)
      Inserts item where it belongs in the tree.
      Parameters:
      item - The item to be inserted
      Returns:
      true If the item is inserted, false if the item was already in the tree.

    • contains

      boolean contains​(E target)
      Determine if an item is in the tree
      Parameters:
      target - Item being sought in tree
      Returns:
      true If the item is in the tree, false otherwise

    • find

      E find​(E target)
      Find an object in the tree
      Parameters:
      target - The item being sought
      Returns:
      A reference to the object in the tree that compares equal as determined by compareTo to the target. If not found null is returned.

    • delete

      E delete​(E target)
      Removes target from tree.
      Parameters:
      target - Item to be removed
      Returns:
      A reference to the object in the tree that compares equal as determined by compareTo to the target. If not found null is returned.

    • remove

      boolean remove​(E target)
      Removes target from tree.
      Parameters:
      target - Item to be removed
      Returns:
      true if the object was in the tree, false otherwise
